<section class="source-band" aria-labelledby="release-summary-heading">
  <div class="section-inner band-grid">
    <div>
      <p class="section-label">Release Summary</p>
      <h2 id="release-summary-heading">FI-v2.25 made the archive easier to find.</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="callout">
      <h3>FI-v2.25 / SEO indexing pass</h3>
      <p>
        FI-v2.25 preserved FI-v2.24 as a recoverable branch, then added the
        first conservative discoverability layer: canonical URL normalization,
        Open Graph metadata, Twitter card metadata, author and generator tags,
        and minimal JSON-LD for the homepage, collection pages, articles, and
        field-log records.
      </p>
      <p>
        The release also added <code>robots.txt</code>, rebuilt
        <code>sitemap.xml</code> around normalized public URLs, included every
        generated ATLAS Report page in the sitemap, and made ATLAS Reports linked
        from Le Signal so crawlers and readers can follow the route without
        JavaScript.
      </p>
      <p class="entry-note">
        Branch: <code>FI-v2.25</code> / commit:
        <a href="{{ site.githubUrl }}/commit/65b8f10">65b8f10</a> / verified
        with <code>npm run pretty</code>, <code>npm run build:site</code>, and
        <code>npm test</code>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

